The paper discusses learning algorithms for multiagent systems, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on computing posterior beliefs and prior beliefs suggests a game theory (cs.GT) and decision making (cs.MA) aspect to the research. Finally, the practical impact of the prior beliefs on long-term performance suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective.
